260
00:17:03.429 --> 00:17:06.514
Hey. excuse me...

261
00:17:06.599 --> 00:17:08.342
We're trying to do the best we can.

262
00:17:08.434 --> 00:17:11.008
We're going to get you out of here as soon as possible.

263
00:17:11.103 --> 00:17:13.725
I just think it's a bunch of bullshit.

264
00:17:19.445 --> 00:17:21.521
Listen. I know you've gone over all this

265
00:17:21.614 --> 00:17:23.405
with Detective Suby...

266
00:17:25.075 --> 00:17:27.910
but would you mind telling me what happened?

267
00:17:29.747 --> 00:17:31.573
It was like I was there.

268
00:17:34.293 --> 00:17:37.744
I knew something bad was going to happen even before it did.

269
00:17:40.132 --> 00:17:42.080
I just felt
wrong. just like...

270
00:17:42.106 --> 00:17:43.323
Just like what?

271
00:17:47.764 --> 00:17:50.516
Look. I know this sounds crazy but...

272
00:17:50.600 --> 00:17:52.972
you guys all heard about Flight 180. right?

273
00:17:53.061 --> 00:17:55.100
The kid who got off the plane?

274
00:17:55.188 --> 00:17:57.311
Well. it happened a year ago. today.

275
00:18:00.276 --> 00:18:02.518
My premonition was just like his.

276
00:18:06.282 --> 00:18:09.485
- What are you talking about?
- Come on.

277
00:18:09.577 --> 00:18:11.237
You must have read about the kid

278
00:18:11.329 --> 00:18:13.238
who had a dream about a plane blowing up.

279
00:18:13.331 --> 00:18:15.240
so he got all his buddies off the plane

280
00:18:15.333 --> 00:18:18.002
and then the thing blew up just like in his dream?

281
00:18:18.085 --> 00:18:20.576
- Yeah.
- But did you hear what happened after?

282
00:18:22.006 --> 00:18:23.915
So a month goes by. right?

283
00:18:24.008 --> 00:18:26.084
Everything seems cool.

284
00:18:27.428 --> 00:18:30.049
But then all the survivors start to die one by one.

285
00:18:30.139 --> 00:18:32.808
'Cause when your number's up. your number's up. right?

286
00:18:34.935 --> 00:18:39.763
You know. some people even say that Death itself was stalking them.

287
00:18:39.857 --> 00:18:42.098
hunting each one down

288
00:18:42.192 --> 00:18:45.727
until they were all...
dead.

289
00:18:49.658 --> 00:18:51.366
Please.

290
00:18:52.953 --> 00:18:55.159
There was one survivor.

291
00:18:57.165 --> 00:18:58.956
Clear Rivers is in a padded room

292
00:18:59.042 --> 00:19:01.747
at the Stonybrook Institution.

293
00:19:01.836 --> 00:19:03.461
Well. that's encouraging.

294
00:19:06.132 --> 00:19:08.919
Okay. you want me to believe that this is true.

295
00:19:09.010 --> 00:19:11.762
that this is happening all over again?

296
00:19:11.846 --> 00:19:13.969
I don't know why we're even here.

297
00:19:15.558 --> 00:19:17.100
What do you want from me?

298
00:19:17.185 --> 00:19:19.936
But if I was never meant to pull over.

299
00:19:20.021 --> 00:19:22.476
we all should have died in that pileup.

300
00:19:22.565 --> 00:19:24.557
Which means Death could be coming for us.

301
00:19:24.650 --> 00:19:26.441
Yeah. like. what if..

302
00:19:26.527 --> 00:19:30.110
..we're all getting that 'Different Strokes' curse or something?

303
00:19:30.197 --> 00:19:32.949
I think you're all are certifiable.

304
00:19:33.033 --> 00:19:35.109
I can't believe I've been listening to this crap.

305
00:19:35.202 --> 00:19:37.954
Let's go.
Let's go. Tim.

306
00:19:38.038 --> 00:19:40.825
Mrs. Carpenter. please.

307
00:19:45.671 --> 00:19:47.497
Kimberly!

308
00:19:48.966 --> 00:19:50.757
Oh baby!

309
00:19:52.010 --> 00:19:54.466
- Are you okay?
- I'm so sorry.

310
00:19:54.554 --> 00:19:56.096
Shh. shh.

311
00:19:56.181 --> 00:19:57.101
You can all go now.

312
00:19:57.127 --> 00:19:58.578
Thank you for your patience.

313
00:20:19.036 --> 00:20:20.994
Could I ask you something?

314
00:20:21.080 --> 00:20:23.488
Anything.

315
00:20:23.583 --> 00:20:26.334
Did Mum ever have any...

316
00:20:26.419 --> 00:20:30.001
I don't know. weird feelings about anything?

317
00:20:31.048 --> 00:20:32.839
What do you mean?

318
00:20:35.386 --> 00:20:39.051
Like visions or premonitions.

319
00:20:40.391 --> 00:20:42.513
Sweetie. are you sure you're okay?

320
00:20:42.601 --> 00:20:45.353
Dad. I know this sounds crazy.

321
00:20:45.437 --> 00:20:47.679
but I'm really scared for the others.

322
00:20:47.773 --> 00:20:51.557
I don't know. I have this really bad feeling.

323
00:20:52.903 --> 00:20:54.397
What?

324
00:20:56.031 --> 00:20:58.070
It's not over yet.

325
00:21:21.013 --> 00:21:23.136
Jesus Christ!

326
00:21:23.224 --> 00:21:25.181
Shit!

327
00:22:55.564 --> 00:22:58.481
Hey. Evan. it's Tawny.

328
00:22:58.567 --> 00:23:00.476
Sorry I haven't called.

329
00:23:00.569 --> 00:23:03.273
Hey. listen. I heard about your lottery win.

330
00:23:03.363 --> 00:23:05.984
Let's hook up.
Call me.

331
00:23:06.074 --> 00:23:08.446
Yeah.

332
00:23:08.535 --> 00:23:10.278
Hi. Evan. it's Nikki.

333
00:23:10.370 --> 00:23:12.493
We met at Tucker's party last year?

334
00:23:12.580 --> 00:23:15.154
I know it's been awhile. but I've been thinking about you.

335
00:23:15.250 --> 00:23:17.954
I just wanted to say congratulations.

336
00:23:18.044 --> 00:23:20.001
So give me a call.

337
00:23:20.088 --> 00:23:22.330
555-0123. Bye.

338
00:23:23.883 --> 00:23:25.840
You little bastard.

339
00:23:25.927 --> 00:23:27.587
Shit.

340
00:23:32.266 --> 00:23:35.351
Come on.
Come on.

341
00:23:42.693 --> 00:23:44.733
Fuck. Fuck.

342
00:23:55.038 --> 00:23:56.830
Come on!

343
00:23:56.915 --> 00:23:58.575
Come on.

344
00:24:04.965 --> 00:24:06.424
Fuck!

345
00:24:06.508 --> 00:24:07.883
Jesus!

346
00:24:15.892 --> 00:24:17.007
Oh!

347
00:24:23.942 --> 00:24:24.897
Hey. this is Evan.

348
00:24:24.923 --> 00:24:25.876
Leave a message.

349
00:24:25.944 --> 00:24:28.435
If you're looking for Rick. I don't know where he is...

350
00:24:28.529 --> 00:24:31.281
..and I don't know when he's coming back. 
Thanks.

351
00:24:31.366 --> 00:24:35.315
Evan. call me when you get in. you lucky fuck!

352
00:25:02.813 --> 00:25:05.979
Come on! Come on!
Come on!

353
00:25:06.066 --> 00:25:07.809
Aah!

354
00:25:38.222 --> 00:25:39.764
Jesus!

355
00:25:44.353 --> 00:25:46.013
Come on.

356
00:25:54.280 --> 00:25:55.690
Aah!

357
00:25:58.450 --> 00:26:00.324
Shit. I'm lucky.

358
00:26:02.746 --> 00:26:04.620
Aah!

359
00:26:07.668 --> 00:26:09.660
Jesus Christ!

360
00:27:35.628 --> 00:27:37.585
No. Mother.

361
00:27:37.672 --> 00:27:40.341
just turn on any station.

362
00:27:40.425 --> 00:27:43.591
Well. I don't know how you missed it. it's been on all day.

363
00:27:43.678 --> 00:27:46.251
Yes. Mother. Channel 4 is fine.

364
00:27:46.347 --> 00:27:47.849
Okay... here it is!

365
00:27:47.875 --> 00:27:49.456
I got to go. okay?

366
00:27:49.517 --> 00:27:51.426
I got to go!

367
00:27:52.478 --> 00:27:54.269
To recap our top story.

368
00:27:54.355 --> 00:27:57.938
Route 23 was backed up for almost nine hours today.

369
00:27:58.025 --> 00:28:01.109
A record-breaking pileup killed an estimated 18 people.

370
00:28:01.195 --> 00:28:04.231
Emergency crews spent hours sifting through the wreckage

371
00:28:04.323 --> 00:28:07.407
hoping to recover any survivors from this tragic collision.

372
00:28:07.493 --> 00:28:10.447
So far police are refusing to release the names of the victims..

373
00:28:10.537 --> 00:28:12.245
..until the families are notified.

374
00:28:12.331 --> 00:28:16.158
The camera of a highway patrol car managed to catch this shocking footage.

375
00:28:16.251 --> 00:28:18.291
- A semi comes...
- Oh my God.

376
00:28:18.378 --> 00:28:20.252
And smashes
into a red SUV.

377
00:28:20.339 --> 00:28:23.921
- The driver of the SUV...
- No. um...

378
00:28:24.009 --> 00:28:25.420
leave it.

379
00:28:25.510 --> 00:28:26.921
...may have saved her life.

380
00:28:27.012 --> 00:28:28.838
He pulled her back at the last second

381
00:28:28.930 --> 00:28:30.970
just as the semi ploughed into the vehicle.

382
00:28:31.057 --> 00:28:32.801
The passengers inside the SUV...

383
00:28:32.892 --> 00:28:34.408
Oh. oh. oh!
You guys see that?!

384
00:28:34.434 --> 00:28:35.704
Shit. I was there. baby!

385
00:28:35.770 --> 00:28:39.720
In other news. a freak accident took the life of a lotto winner.

386
00:28:39.816 --> 00:28:41.643
- Friends say Evan Lewis...
- Hey. shh.

387
00:28:41.734 --> 00:28:45.435
Was on top of the world after recently winning $250.000.

388
00:28:45.530 --> 00:28:48.199
But in tragic turn of events. Lewis died today

389
00:28:48.282 --> 00:28:50.856
while trying to escape a fire in his apartment.

390
00:28:50.952 --> 00:28:52.695
He managed to make it out of the building..

391
00:28:52.787 --> 00:28:56.948
..but somehow the ladder on the fire escape slipped and impaled him.

392
00:28:57.041 --> 00:28:59.532
Investigators believe Lewis died instantly.

393
00:29:06.759 --> 00:29:09.760
Come in.

394
00:29:11.597 --> 00:29:13.091
Hey. buddy.

395
00:29:14.600 --> 00:29:17.435
I want you to take this so you can get some sleep.

396
00:29:19.271 --> 00:29:22.604
And then tomorrow it's off to the dentist. which I know you love.

397
00:29:24.276 --> 00:29:26.103
Now. get some rest.

398
00:29:30.615 --> 00:29:33.237
- Mum.
- Yeah?

399
00:29:33.326 --> 00:29:35.366
You think those guys were BSing us today?

400
00:29:35.453 --> 00:29:37.197
Yeah.

401
00:29:37.288 --> 00:29:39.696
Some people just need some rewiring. that's all.

402
00:29:41.126 --> 00:29:42.620
Lights out.

