00:31:41.034 --> 00:31:43.157
At the request of the patient.

444
00:31:43.244 --> 00:31:45.237
you'll relinquish any sharp objects

445
00:31:45.330 --> 00:31:47.655
such as: 'nail files. pencils. pens.

446
00:31:47.749 --> 00:31:50.666
safety pins. bobby pins. your necklace.

447
00:31:50.752 --> 00:31:53.325
matches. lighters. belts. belt buckles.

448
00:31:53.421 --> 00:31:56.505
earrings. hair clips. glasses. shoelaces.

449
00:31:56.591 --> 00:31:59.627
paper clips. watches. money clip. pocket knives.

450
00:31:59.719 --> 00:32:02.340
food. drinks. keys. cell phone... '

451
00:32:02.430 --> 00:32:04.588
You have a cell phone on you?

452
00:32:04.682 --> 00:32:07.599
'... poisons. pills. medications.'

453
00:32:07.685 --> 00:32:10.258
Great. And let me see your nails.

454
00:32:10.354 --> 00:32:12.928
Good.
Then I think we're all done.

455
00:32:13.023 --> 00:32:14.933
Wait.

456
00:32:15.025 --> 00:32:16.935
Is she dangerous or something?

457
00:32:17.027 --> 00:32:18.984
No. honey. she expects you are.

458
00:32:21.615 --> 00:32:24.782
No. no. no.

459
00:32:24.868 --> 00:32:28.071
Get him off me.
Get him off me!

460
00:32:35.629 --> 00:32:38.202
How long are they gonna keep her locked up like this?

461
00:32:38.298 --> 00:32:39.701
Depends on her. I guess.

462
00:32:39.727 --> 00:32:40.779
She's voluntary.

463
00:33:08.828 --> 00:33:11.449
- Clear Rivers?
- Don't come any closer.

464
00:33:19.755 --> 00:33:23.254
They told me you had something to do with the crash on Route 23.

465
00:33:23.342 --> 00:33:26.259
Look. I don't know how to explain it.

466
00:33:26.345 --> 00:33:29.630
but I saw the pileup before it happened.

467
00:33:31.141 --> 00:33:33.217
And I saved some people.

468
00:33:33.310 --> 00:33:35.635
And now you think Death is after you.

469
00:33:37.439 --> 00:33:39.478
Nice work.

470
00:33:39.566 --> 00:33:42.816
Maybe if you're real lucky. you'll wind up in here with me.

471
00:33:44.404 --> 00:33:46.064
Anything else?

472
00:33:46.156 --> 00:33:48.611
One of the people died in a freak accident last night.

473
00:33:48.700 --> 00:33:50.776
What if the other people are in danger. too?

474
00:33:50.869 --> 00:33:53.241
If you put them on the list. they're already dead.

475
00:33:53.329 --> 00:33:55.618
List? What list?

476
00:33:55.707 --> 00:33:57.865
Death's list.

477
00:34:00.336 --> 00:34:02.578
The survivors of Flight 180

478
00:34:02.672 --> 00:34:04.914
died in the exact order

479
00:34:05.008 --> 00:34:07.795
they were originally meant to die in the plane crash.

480
00:34:08.970 --> 00:34:10.962
That was Death's original design.

481
00:34:12.348 --> 00:34:13.972
The list.

482
00:34:14.058 --> 00:34:16.514
I was supposed to die in that crash with my friends.

483
00:34:16.602 --> 00:34:18.262
So you're telling me that I'm next?

484
00:34:18.354 --> 00:34:20.512
You said someone else died last night.

485
00:34:20.606 --> 00:34:22.646
That means someone must have intervened.

486
00:34:22.733 --> 00:34:26.980
Officer Burke pulled me away from the crash that killed my friends.

487
00:34:27.071 --> 00:34:28.944
Congratulations.

488
00:34:29.031 --> 00:34:31.604
You'll be the last to go.

489
00:34:31.700 --> 00:34:34.274
But don't worry. once the others are dead.

490
00:34:34.369 --> 00:34:35.994
it'll come back for you.

491
00:34:37.331 --> 00:34:39.370
It always does.

492
00:34:40.667 --> 00:34:42.411
This doesn't make sense.

493
00:34:42.502 --> 00:34:46.832
You said that you die in the order you're originally meant to.

494
00:34:46.923 --> 00:34:50.672
But my friends died last in my premonition. not first.

495
00:34:50.760 --> 00:34:52.718
Wait.

496
00:34:53.847 --> 00:34:56.172
Died last?

497
00:34:58.184 --> 00:35:00.058
Backwards.

498
00:35:00.145 --> 00:35:02.184
Are you sure?

499
00:35:04.107 --> 00:35:05.898
In my premonition

500
00:35:05.984 --> 00:35:07.893
that Nora woman and her kid died.

501
00:35:07.986 --> 00:35:11.105
Then Evan. then me and my friends.

502
00:35:14.116 --> 00:35:16.275
Why is this even happening to me?

503
00:35:20.790 --> 00:35:23.115
That's what Alex used to ask himself.

504
00:35:24.794 --> 00:35:27.082
So. what am I supposed to do?

505
00:35:27.171 --> 00:35:29.128
Clear.

506
00:35:30.799 --> 00:35:32.591
Watch out for the signs.

507
00:35:32.676 --> 00:35:34.384
What?

508
00:35:36.805 --> 00:35:39.842
Have you ever seen anything creepy or ominous?

509
00:35:39.933 --> 00:35:42.638
An in-your-face irony kind of thing?

510
00:35:44.980 --> 00:35:47.435
The songs on the radio.

511
00:35:47.524 --> 00:35:50.478
Yeah. the guy in the beer truck. everything on the road.

512
00:35:50.569 --> 00:35:52.810
Well. don't ignore it.

513
00:35:52.904 --> 00:35:56.522
Recognizing those signs usually means the difference between life and death.

514
00:35:56.616 --> 00:35:59.072
You got to help me.

515
00:35:59.160 --> 00:36:00.785
I don't have to do anything.

516
00:36:00.870 --> 00:36:02.578
But you beat it.

517
00:36:02.664 --> 00:36:04.407
Take a look around.

518
00:36:04.499 --> 00:36:06.456
What did I beat. Kimberly?

519
00:36:08.795 --> 00:36:12.045
If you were smart. you'd save yourself and just forget about the others.

520
00:36:12.131 --> 00:36:13.234
How can you say that?

521
00:36:13.260 --> 00:36:14.730
You have a responsibility.

522
00:36:14.801 --> 00:36:16.923
My friends are dead.

523
00:36:17.011 --> 00:36:18.968
That's how I can say that.

524
00:36:20.848 --> 00:36:24.182
This is what happened to Alex when I was responsible for him.

525
00:36:25.311 --> 00:36:27.268
Get out.

526
00:36:27.354 --> 00:36:29.727
Before you hurt me or yourself.

527
00:36:33.652 --> 00:36:36.487
- Alright. you know what?
- What?

528
00:36:36.572 --> 00:36:37.947
I think you're a coward.

529
00:36:38.032 --> 00:36:39.656
You hide out in here because you're

530
00:36:39.742 --> 00:36:42.945
too damn bitter and selfish to help any other person.

531
00:36:43.036 --> 00:36:44.946
In my opinion. you're already dead.

532
00:37:22.950 --> 00:37:24.990
I tried calling you last night.

533
00:37:25.077 --> 00:37:27.070
but your father said you were sleeping.

534
00:37:27.163 --> 00:37:28.871
- Evan Lewis is dead.
- Yeah.

535
00:37:28.956 --> 00:37:32.242
I've been getting calls all morning from everyone who was on the on-ramp.

536
00:37:32.334 --> 00:37:34.457
We're meeting tonight at my apartment.

537
00:37:34.545 --> 00:37:37.795
Wait. so...
you believe all this Death stuff?

538
00:37:39.008 --> 00:37:41.581
Well. at first. no. I didn't.

539
00:37:41.677 --> 00:37:43.753
Until last year when I was dispatched

540
00:37:43.846 --> 00:37:46.134
to clean up one of the Flight 180 survivors.

541
00:37:46.223 --> 00:37:47.966
Clean up. I don't...

542
00:37:52.521 --> 00:37:55.012
- Did you see that?
- See what?

543
00:37:55.107 --> 00:37:57.598
- Pigeons.
- Pigeons?

544
00:37:57.692 --> 00:37:59.602
- It's a sign.
- A sign of what?

545
00:37:59.694 --> 00:38:01.438
If Clear's right about the order.

546
00:38:01.530 --> 00:38:04.696
then Nora and Tim are going to be attacked by pigeons.

547
00:38:04.783 --> 00:38:06.277
I'm not following you.

548
00:38:06.368 --> 00:38:08.028
They're next on Death's list.

549
00:38:08.119 --> 00:38:10.575
If we don't find them. they're going to die.

550
00:38:58.293 --> 00:39:00.286
The doctor's ready for you. now.

551
00:39:00.378 --> 00:39:02.205
If he gives me the gas

552
00:39:02.297 --> 00:39:04.373
and I wake up with my pants unbuttoned...

553
00:39:04.466 --> 00:39:08.000
- we ain't paying.
- Tim.

554
00:39:15.435 --> 00:39:16.498
There you are.

555
00:39:16.524 --> 00:39:19.409
What happened to you yesterday. Tim?

556
00:39:19.480 --> 00:39:20.227
We missed you in here.

557
00:39:20.315 --> 00:39:22.852
We got hung up by that accident on Route 23.

558
00:39:22.942 --> 00:39:25.611
Good Lord.
How lucky that you're okay.

559
00:39:27.321 --> 00:39:29.444
Your mum says you've been having some pain lately.

560
00:39:29.532 --> 00:39:31.738
Not really.

561
00:39:56.975 --> 00:39:58.932
I'm disappointed. Tim.

562
00:39:59.019 --> 00:40:00.347
Does your mum know you've been smoking?

563
00:40:00.437 --> 00:40:03.604
Uh-huh.
Ow.

564
00:40:03.690 --> 00:40:05.813
Yeah. that one's going to have to be filled.

565
00:40:07.194 --> 00:40:09.020
Damn those pigeons.

566
00:40:09.112 --> 00:40:12.528
How many times am I going to have to replace those goddamn windows?

567
00:40:14.993 --> 00:40:17.780
We can't do it. boss. we can't do it!

568
00:40:17.871 --> 00:40:20.492
This will only sting for a moment.

569
00:40:20.582 --> 00:40:22.788
Open big.

570
00:40:22.875 --> 00:40:24.453
Little bit wider.

571
00:40:24.544 --> 00:40:26.453
Wider.

572
00:40:26.546 --> 00:40:29.001
Okay.

573
00:40:30.258 --> 00:40:32.297
Oh God.

574
00:40:32.385 --> 00:40:34.212
How do they expect me to...

575
00:40:34.303 --> 00:40:36.877
Would you rather just have the laughing gas?

576
00:40:36.973 --> 00:40:39.214
- Yeah.
- Okay.

577
00:40:39.308 --> 00:40:41.135
Jean. I'm going to need you in here.

578
00:40:43.729 --> 00:40:45.935
You'll have to speak up. there's too much noise.

579
00:40:48.025 --> 00:40:50.979
What?!
I can't hear you!

580
00:40:51.070 --> 00:40:53.146
Excuse me. what?!

581
00:40:54.531 --> 00:40:57.236
Yes. the sixth at 2:00 P.M.

582
00:40:57.326 --> 00:40:59.995
Jean! Let me get this started.

583
00:41:02.122 --> 00:41:03.865
Tim. you'll be awake. a little groggy.

584
00:41:03.957 --> 00:41:06.080
but you're not going to be able to move much.

585
00:41:31.359 --> 00:41:32.440
Okay. great. thanks.

586
00:41:32.466 --> 00:41:33.709
Alright. turn around.

587
00:41:33.778 --> 00:41:37.028
The cleaning lady said they're at the Ellis Medical Complex off of 14th.

588
00:41:40.743 --> 00:41:43.744
God damn it anyway.

589
00:41:51.086 --> 00:41:51.882
Okay. I got it.

590
00:41:51.908 --> 00:41:53.234
I can't find a box!

591
00:41:55.257 --> 00:41:57.048
Not again. Careful.

592
00:42:38.424 --> 00:42:40.084
There we go.

593
00:42:49.435 --> 00:42:51.427
Jean.
how's Tim doing in there?

594
00:42:56.442 --> 00:42:58.233
What did he say about your tooth?

595
00:42:58.319 --> 00:43:00.607
- Did he say...
- I can't remember.

596
00:43:00.696 --> 00:43:02.356
- Nora!
- The pigeons!

597
00:43:02.448 --> 00:43:04.689
What? Pigeons?

598
00:43:06.577 --> 00:43:08.486
Hey. whoa. whoa!
Kid. kid!

599
00:43:10.580 --> 00:43:12.288
- No-oo!
- Tim!

600
00:43:12.374 --> 00:43:13.572
Look out!

601
00:43:15.335 --> 00:43:16.539
Stay back. stay back!

602
00:43:16.565 --> 00:43:17.768
No! Please. no!

603
00:43:36.064 --> 00:43:37.000
Nora's not coming.

604
00:43:37.026 --> 00:43:38.377
She won't leave her son.

605
00:43:38.441 --> 00:43:39.801
No. but she's next...

606
00:43:39.827 --> 00:43:42.416
Right now I don't think she cares.

607
00:44:01.422 --> 00:44:03.663
This is really happening again. isn't it?

608
00:44:06.009 --> 00:44:07.967
I hoped we'd get there..

609
00:44:08.053 --> 00:44:09.962
..and they'd be fine.

610
00:44:10.055 --> 00:44:12.297
..and Clear Rivers was just full of shit...

611
00:44:12.391 --> 00:44:16.175
..and Evan Lewis' death was just some freak accident.

612
00:44:18.188 --> 00:44:20.346
But we're all going to die. aren't we?

613
00:44:24.694 --> 00:44:26.687
I'm so scared.

614
00:44:28.114 --> 00:44:30.652
I know you didn't ask for any of this...

615
00:44:31.826 --> 00:44:34.400
but I don't think you have it in you to quit either.

616
00:44:42.879 --> 00:44:44.670
A second one just died.

617
00:44:44.756 --> 00:44:46.547
A 15-year-old kid.

618
00:44:48.551 --> 00:44:50.709
I hope you're ready for this.

619
00:45:02.356 --> 00:45:03.850
It's this way.

620
00:45:06.193 --> 00:45:08.649
How is this guy going to help us anyway?

621
00:45:08.737 --> 00:45:13.197
He seemed to know a hell of a lot more about Death than he ever told us.

622
00:45:17.371 --> 00:45:19.328
Shouldn't we knock first?

623
00:45:19.414 --> 00:45:21.703
He probably already knows we're coming.

624
00:46:09.004 --> 00:46:10.997
Hello. Clear.

625
00:46:17.012 --> 00:46:18.755
I've been expecting you.

626
00:46:18.847 --> 00:46:20.804
Oh my God.

627
00:46:22.392 --> 00:46:23.450
That's Evan Lewis.

628
00:46:23.476 --> 00:46:25.122
Come to pick my brain?

629
00:46:25.187 --> 00:46:28.353
Just a simple question and we'll leave you alone with your new friend.

630
00:46:30.025 --> 00:46:31.982
Dead...

631
00:46:32.068 --> 00:46:34.855
yet still fresh.

632
00:46:36.281 --> 00:46:38.320
Look. we drove a long way to get here.

633
00:46:38.408 --> 00:46:40.447
so if you happen to know how to stop Death.

634
00:46:40.535 --> 00:46:42.278
it would be really great if you told us.

635
00:46:43.371 --> 00:46:44.996
You can't cheat Death.

636
00:46:45.081 --> 00:46:47.833
- There are no escapes.
- Bullshit.

637
00:46:47.917 --> 00:46:50.788
You told me Death has a distinct design.

638
00:46:50.878 --> 00:46:54.164
But Alex and I cheated Death. not once but dozens of times.

639
00:46:54.257 --> 00:46:56.712
The design is flawed. it can be beaten.

640
00:46:56.801 --> 00:46:59.505
Such fire in you now.

641
00:46:59.595 --> 00:47:02.169
People are always most alive..

642
00:47:02.264 --> 00:47:03.972
..just before they die.

643
00:47:04.058 --> 00:47:05.801
Don't you think?

644
00:47:22.659 --> 00:47:23.940
Look. please...

645
00:47:30.375 --> 00:47:33.661
if you know of anything that could help us.

646
00:47:33.753 --> 00:47:35.711
what harm could it do?

647
00:47:36.756 --> 00:47:40.256
Only new life can defeat Death.

648
00:47:40.343 --> 00:47:42.466
What the hell does that mean?

649
00:47:44.389 --> 00:47:46.880
Some people say there's a balance to everything.

650
00:47:48.059 --> 00:47:52.178
For every life there's a death. and for every death there is a life.

651
00:47:52.271 --> 00:47:55.023
But the introduction of life that was not meant to be.

652
00:47:55.108 --> 00:47:57.480
that can invalidate the list.

653
00:47:57.568 --> 00:48:00.854
force Death to start anew.

654
00:48:08.829 --> 00:48:11.285
You have to follow the signs...

655
00:48:11.373 --> 00:48:13.200
Kimberly.

656
00:48:15.502 --> 00:48:17.495
How do you know my name?

657
00:48:31.435 --> 00:48:33.723
- Whoa! 
- Wait a second.

658
00:48:33.812 --> 00:48:36.813
'New life defeats death'?
'Follow the signs'?

659
00:48:36.898 --> 00:48:38.807
Where did you find that guy?

660
00:48:38.900 --> 00:48:40.644
I thought he was supposed to help us.

661
00:48:40.735 --> 00:48:42.146
not freak us out.

662
00:48:47.367 --> 00:48:48.991
What the fuck are you thinking?!

663
00:48:51.037 --> 00:48:54.323
I'm thinking suck on my junk. bee-atch.

664
00:48:54.415 --> 00:48:56.207
Little punk.

665
00:49:08.304 --> 00:49:10.095
What is it?

666
00:49:10.181 --> 00:49:12.553
What did you see?

667
00:49:26.071 --> 00:49:28.194
You have to tell us. what did you see?

668
00:49:28.282 --> 00:49:29.336
Kimberly. look at me!

669
00:49:29.362 --> 00:49:30.465
You have to tell us.

670
00:49:30.534 --> 00:49:32.657
What did you see?!

671
00:49:35.831 --> 00:49:37.622
I was driving a white van.

672
00:49:37.707 --> 00:49:40.033
I don't know. I must have lost control.

673
00:49:40.127 --> 00:49:41.953
because I crashed into a lake.

674
00:49:42.045 --> 00:49:44.168
- And I drowned.
- You were there?

675
00:49:44.256 --> 00:49:47.173
I can practically taste the water in my mouth.

676
00:49:50.345 --> 00:49:52.136
Wait. remember. the on-ramp?

677
00:49:52.222 --> 00:49:54.891
There was a pregnant woman in a white delivery van.

678
00:49:54.974 --> 00:49:58.308
He said only new life can defeat death.

679
00:49:59.854 --> 00:50:01.348
If she gives birth to a baby

680
00:50:01.439 --> 00:50:03.396
that would've died in that car crash...

681
00:50:03.483 --> 00:50:06.104
a brand new soul that was never part of Death's design...

682
00:50:06.194 --> 00:50:07.771
It throws the whole list out of whack

683
00:50:07.862 --> 00:50:10.068
and we start over with a clean slate.

684
00:50:10.156 --> 00:50:11.896
It seems like a reach. don't you think?

685
00:50:11.922 --> 00:50:13.182
What else could it mean?

686
00:50:13.242 --> 00:50:15.318
We have to find the pregnant lady's number.

687
00:50:15.411 --> 00:50:15.869
I don't have it.

688
00:50:15.895 --> 00:50:16.811
She never came to the station.

689
00:50:16.871 --> 00:50:21.034
We have to warn her about the lake so she can stay alive to have the baby.

690
00:50:21.125 --> 00:50:22.901
That'll be an easy conversation to have.

691
00:50:22.927 --> 00:50:24.269
How are we gonna find her?

692
00:50:24.336 --> 00:50:25.914
There could be thousands of white vans in the state.

693
00:50:26.005 --> 00:50:27.249
Hey!

694
00:50:28.340 --> 00:50:30.131
I'm a cop. remember?

695
00:50:33.595 --> 00:50:35.173
Wait. that's it.

696
00:50:38.183 --> 00:50:39.974
Got it.

697
00:50:42.229 --> 00:50:44.517
With the plate number I can put out an APB.

698
00:50:44.606 --> 00:50:46.682
Here we go.

699
00:50:46.775 --> 00:50:48.684
The vehicle is a delivery van

700
00:50:48.777 --> 00:50:51.184
registered to Marcus and Isabella Hudson.

701
00:50:52.405 --> 00:50:54.528
We should pick them up pretty quickly.

702
00:50:54.616 --> 00:50:56.442
Come on. let's get to the meeting.

703
00:51:11.215 --> 00:51:13.042
Hey. hold the door!

704
00:51:14.427 --> 00:51:16.384
Hey. let go of my shoe!

705
00:51:16.470 --> 00:51:18.214
Give me my shoe!

706
00:51:24.228 --> 00:51:27.264
I wrote to management two weeks ago about these friggin' bumpers.

707
00:51:29.233 --> 00:51:31.391
Is that dogshit. dude?

708
00:51:34.571 --> 00:51:36.315
Eww.

709
00:51:41.578 --> 00:51:43.736
Oh. you got something on your...

710
00:51:46.875 --> 00:51:48.292
It's still there. bro'.

711
00:51:48.318 --> 00:51:50.103
Here. I can get it for you.

712
00:51:51.212 --> 00:51:53.122
No. it's alright.

713
00:51:54.758 --> 00:51:57.249
I'll do it if you want me to do it.

714
00:52:00.680 --> 00:52:02.471
Just let... I'll...
Let me do it.

715
00:52:04.517 --> 00:52:06.344
What?

716
00:52:07.603 --> 00:52:09.395
Hey. man. how you doing?

717
00:52:09.480 --> 00:52:11.687
Listen. any word on that white van yet?

718
00:52:13.359 --> 00:52:15.352
Okay. keep checking.

719
00:52:25.538 --> 00:52:27.329
Does anybody have a Valium?

720
00:52:27.414 --> 00:52:29.324
Oh. yeah.

721
00:52:29.416 --> 00:52:31.160
Here.

722
00:52:31.251 --> 00:52:33.659
You're just going to want to take half of that.

723
00:52:33.754 --> 00:52:35.248
Keep 'em coming.

724
00:52:38.008 --> 00:52:39.668
If what you're saying is true.

725
00:52:39.760 --> 00:52:41.337
that means I'm next.

726
00:52:41.428 --> 00:52:44.001
This is crazy. people. come on.

727
00:52:44.097 --> 00:52:46.173
First Death is stalking us.

728
00:52:46.266 --> 00:52:48.638
and now premonitions? What?

729
00:52:48.727 --> 00:52:50.387
You're not next. Nora.

730
00:52:50.479 --> 00:52:52.223
Nobody has to be next.

731
00:52:52.249 --> 00:52:53.754
That's the point.

732
00:52:53.815 --> 00:52:56.982
We need to help each other in order to get through this.

733
00:52:57.068 --> 00:52:58.693
This cannot be happening.

734
00:52:58.778 --> 00:53:00.522
See. because my career is at a peak

735
00:53:00.613 --> 00:53:02.653
and I finally met a quality guy.

736
00:53:02.740 --> 00:53:04.318
I just bought a house.

737
00:53:04.409 --> 00:53:06.448
Maybe if you shut the fuck up. you'll live.

738
00:53:07.870 --> 00:53:09.863
Like I'm going to take advice from you.

739
00:53:09.956 --> 00:53:12.661
Okay. look. if you know what to look for.

740
00:53:12.750 --> 00:53:14.328
you have a fighting chance.

741
00:53:14.419 --> 00:53:17.834
If I call and say. I don't know... subway...

742
00:53:17.922 --> 00:53:20.211
Get to a high-rise fast.

743
00:53:22.218 --> 00:53:25.337
A place where no subway could ever possibly go.

744
00:53:25.429 --> 00:53:27.386
Get it?

745
00:53:30.226 --> 00:53:32.847
Okay. you guys. listen...

746
00:53:32.937 --> 00:53:35.013
just because Kimberly has these visions.

747
00:53:35.105 --> 00:53:36.849
it doesn't mean we're not all capable

748
00:53:36.940 --> 00:53:38.684
of seeing signs to some extent.

749
00:53:38.776 --> 00:53:40.483
Okay. okay. look.

750
00:53:40.569 --> 00:53:42.028
I gotta call bullshit.

751
00:53:42.112 --> 00:53:43.856
I mean. I've sat here and listened

752
00:53:43.947 --> 00:53:45.856
to all your theories and all your stories.

753
00:53:45.949 --> 00:53:47.989
and I think it's just all bullshit.

754
00:53:48.076 --> 00:53:49.784
Call it what you want!

755
00:53:49.870 --> 00:53:51.167
It'll keep your arse alive.

756
00:53:51.193 --> 00:53:52.730
Darlin'. my arse is alive!

757
00:53:52.789 --> 00:53:54.698
Has been all day.

758
00:53:55.917 --> 00:53:58.206
There is nobody after us
but you.

759
00:53:58.295 --> 00:54:00.501
trying to make us all crazy.

760
00:54:14.686 --> 00:54:16.393
I should have seen that coming.

761
00:54:16.479 --> 00:54:18.021
Yeah.

762
00:54:18.106 --> 00:54:20.347
If Death is out to get you.

763
00:54:20.441 --> 00:54:22.481
why don't you get the hell away from us?

764
00:54:22.568 --> 00:54:24.691
She's the only one that's dealt with this before.

765
00:54:24.779 --> 00:54:26.818
We need to look out for each other from now on.

766
00:54:26.906 --> 00:54:28.448
Sleep in shifts.

767
00:54:28.532 --> 00:54:30.904
We need to safe-proof this death-trap.

768
00:54:40.377 --> 00:54:42.500
Get you to step out of the van. miss?

769
00:54:42.588 --> 00:54:44.580
Are you kidding me?

770
00:54:44.673 --> 00:54:45.453
What did I do?

771
00:54:45.479 --> 00:54:47.818
This vehicle's been reported stolen.

772
00:54:49.886 --> 00:54:52.009
Ohh!

773
00:54:52.097 --> 00:54:54.339
Screw this.
I'm going for a smoke.

774
00:54:54.433 --> 00:54:57.006
No. no. no. it's not safe out there.

775
00:54:57.102 --> 00:54:59.675
So. Nora's got to bite it before me anyhow. huh?

776
00:54:59.771 --> 00:55:02.772
Oh. you people have no sense of humor.

777
00:55:09.489 --> 00:55:11.814
Nora. you okay?

778
00:55:13.826 --> 00:55:16.115
Four years ago my husband died.

779
00:55:17.163 --> 00:55:19.286
Now Tim.
There's nothing left for me.

780
00:55:19.374 --> 00:55:21.283
Don't say that. okay?

781
00:55:21.375 --> 00:55:23.949
If it is my time to go and be in heaven...

782
00:55:24.045 --> 00:55:26.618
with my family. I can accept that.

783
00:55:26.714 --> 00:55:28.588
You got to trust me.

784
00:55:28.614 --> 00:55:30.487
We can fight this.

785
00:55:30.551 --> 00:55:32.460
If we just stick together long enough

786
00:55:32.553 --> 00:55:34.131
for her to have her baby...

787
00:55:34.221 --> 00:55:36.677
If you'll excuse me. I have a funeral to plan.

788
00:55:37.850 --> 00:55:39.510
Nora.

789
00:55:42.354 --> 00:55:44.146
What do you think you're doing?

790
00:55:44.231 --> 00:55:45.410
I'm finished. I'm out.

791
00:55:45.436 --> 00:55:46.829
Don't leave. Eugene.

792
00:55:46.900 --> 00:55:48.810
Look. look.

793
00:55:48.902 --> 00:55:50.942
I control my life. alright?

794
00:55:51.029 --> 00:55:53.947
Not some crazy list that Death has put together.

795
00:55:55.200 --> 00:55:57.358
I'll be sure to carve that into your tombstone.

796
00:55:57.452 --> 00:56:00.026
Whatever. You may be able to scare these people.

797
00:56:00.122 --> 00:56:01.359
I'm not buying that shit.

798
00:56:01.385 --> 00:56:02.472
Be careful. man.

799
00:56:02.541 --> 00:56:04.118
- Hey.
- What?

800
00:56:04.209 --> 00:56:07.329
Even if you don't believe. give this to Nora.

801
00:56:18.348 --> 00:56:20.174
I'm just going to put this in the...

802
00:56:21.351 --> 00:56:23.058
closet.

803
00:56:52.297 --> 00:56:54.171
Sorry.

804
00:57:10.523 --> 00:57:12.481
Whoa.

805
00:57:22.493 --> 00:57:24.486
Man with hooks?

806
00:57:25.663 --> 00:57:27.455
Man with hooks.

807
00:57:27.540 --> 00:57:29.948
Hey. I think I see a man with hooks.

808
00:57:31.752 --> 00:57:33.330
Is that...

809
00:57:34.839 --> 00:57:36.713
- a sign?
- Oh my God.

810
00:57:36.799 --> 00:57:38.459
- Do you guys see that?
- He's right.

811
00:57:38.551 --> 00:57:39.961
- The phone.
- Shit.

812
00:58:01.114 --> 00:58:02.988
What the fuck?

813
00:58:13.501 --> 00:58:15.079
- Hello?
- Nora!

814
00:58:15.170 --> 00:58:18.087
- Who is this?
- Can you hear me?!

815
00:58:18.173 --> 00:58:20.877
Officer Burke. I can't...

816
00:58:20.967 --> 00:58:22.592
I can't hear you!
What?!

817
00:58:22.677 --> 00:58:23.875
What does he...
What?!

818
00:58:23.970 --> 00:58:26.093
A man with hooks is going to kill you.

819
00:58:26.180 --> 00:58:27.639
- What. what?
- Oh...

820
00:58:27.724 --> 00:58:29.384
What is it. Nora?

821
00:58:31.978 --> 00:58:33.436
No!

822
00:58:33.521 --> 00:58:35.810
- Wait. wait!
- Let go!

823
00:58:35.898 --> 00:58:37.772
Wait. wait. Nora!

824
00:58:37.859 --> 00:58:38.739
Get me out of here!

825
00:58:38.765 --> 00:58:39.876
Will you stop it?!

826
00:58:39.944 --> 00:58:41.272
Let me help!

827
00:58:41.362 --> 00:58:42.737
Let me go!

828
00:58:50.079 --> 00:58:52.285
Let go of me!

829
00:58:59.213 --> 00:59:01.122
Kat!

830
00:59:12.309 --> 00:59:14.218
Help me!

831
00:59:14.311 --> 00:59:16.884
- Wait!
- I don't want to die!

832
00:59:29.659 --> 00:59:31.616
Aah!
Let me out of here.

833
00:59:33.788 --> 00:59:34.680
I got it. thanks.

834
00:59:34.706 --> 00:59:35.806
They found the van.

835
00:59:35.873 --> 00:59:38.791
Isabella's being held at the Greenwood Lake sheriff's station.

836
00:59:38.876 --> 00:59:41.118
I'm in control of my life!

837
00:59:41.212 --> 00:59:41.979
Kiss my arse!

838
00:59:42.005 --> 00:59:43.479
Eugene. what is it?

839
00:59:43.547 --> 00:59:44.313
I control my life!

840
00:59:44.339 --> 00:59:45.530
What happened. Eugene?

841
00:59:45.591 --> 00:59:48.296
- You hear me. you Reaper cocksucker?!
- Calm down.

842
00:59:48.386 --> 00:59:49.662
What happened?
Where's Nora?

843
00:59:49.688 --> 00:59:50.736
Back the fuck up!

844
00:59:50.805 --> 00:59:52.025
Whoa. whoa. okay!

845
00:59:52.051 --> 00:59:53.700
Back the fuck up!

846
00:59:53.766 --> 00:59:54.797
Eugene. what's wrong?

847
00:59:54.823 --> 00:59:56.246
Just tell us what happened.

848
00:59:56.310 --> 00:59:58.349
Alright. give me the gun. Eugene.

849
00:59:58.437 --> 00:59:59.475
Give me the gun.

850
00:59:59.501 --> 01:00:00.668
No! Fuck no!

851
01:00:00.731 --> 01:00:03.815
Eugene. you just got to relax. bro'. okay?

852
01:00:03.901 --> 01:00:05.940
You just got to calm down. man.

853
01:00:06.028 --> 01:00:06.724
Give me the gun.

854
01:00:06.750 --> 01:00:07.879
Give me the gun. Eugene!

855
01:00:07.946 --> 01:00:08.898
No. no. no. no!

856
01:00:08.924 --> 01:00:10.889
Don't do it! Don't do it!

857
01:00:10.949 --> 01:00:12.112
I ain't going out like that.

858
01:00:12.138 --> 01:00:13.050
