909
01:00:54.200 --> 01:00:56.276
Is this safe. guys?

910
01:00:56.368 --> 01:00:58.824
I mean. someone in this car is about to get whacked.

911
01:00:58.913 --> 01:01:01.368
Do the rest of us really feel like sitting next to him?

912
01:01:01.457 --> 01:01:03.330
Or her?

913
01:01:04.668 --> 01:01:06.328
Hopefully her.

914
01:01:07.588 --> 01:01:09.461
Okay. guys. let's not panic.

915
01:01:09.548 --> 01:01:12.169
- Isabella's safe.
- How do you know?

916
01:01:13.385 --> 01:01:15.627
You said she was going to drive into a lake.

917
01:01:15.721 --> 01:01:18.556
How can she if she's in protective custody?

918
01:01:26.189 --> 01:01:27.767
Look at me.

919
01:01:27.857 --> 01:01:29.850
Come on.

920
01:01:29.943 --> 01:01:33.570
Does it look like I'm in the condition to commit grand theft auto?

921
01:01:33.596 --> 01:01:34.502
This is insane.

922
01:01:34.572 --> 01:01:36.481
Look. hopefully the district judge

923
01:01:36.574 --> 01:01:39.492
will have it all sorted out by Monday morning. okay?

924
01:01:46.042 --> 01:01:47.999
Marcus.

925
01:01:48.085 --> 01:01:50.659
Marcus. Marcus.

926
01:01:50.755 --> 01:01:52.996
When I get out of here. I am going to sue his...

927
01:01:55.051 --> 01:01:57.968
- Oh my God.
- What. what now?

928
01:01:58.053 --> 01:02:00.011
My water just broke.

929
01:02:00.097 --> 01:02:02.006
- What?
- My water. it just broke.

930
01:02:02.099 --> 01:02:03.580
I'm gonna have my baby.

931
01:02:03.606 --> 01:02:04.829
No. not here.

932
01:02:04.893 --> 01:02:06.326
No. you can't do this to me.

933
01:02:06.352 --> 01:02:07.836
Don't just stand there!

934
01:02:07.896 --> 01:02:09.118
Get me to a hospital!

935
01:02:09.144 --> 01:02:11.006
Give me a second to think!

936
01:02:11.066 --> 01:02:14.316
I am not going to have my baby in a jail cell!

937
01:02:14.403 --> 01:02:16.063
Get me to the hospital!

938
01:02:16.154 --> 01:02:18.028
Okay. okay!

939
01:02:18.115 --> 01:02:21.199
Sheriff Perry. this is Deputy Adams. come back.

940
01:02:22.536 --> 01:02:23.512
God. I need the car!

941
01:02:23.538 --> 01:02:25.099
Sheriff Perry. I need the car!

942
01:02:25.163 --> 01:02:26.305
My van! My van!

943
01:02:26.331 --> 01:02:27.395
Take my van!

944
01:02:29.709 --> 01:02:31.334
Okay. Okay.

945
01:02:31.419 --> 01:02:33.495
Yeah. we'll go.
We'll go.

946
01:02:33.588 --> 01:02:35.545
Yeah. we'll go.

947
01:02:39.219 --> 01:02:40.962
Come on. come on!

948
01:02:45.725 --> 01:02:48.216
Y'all want to hear something crazy?

949
01:02:48.311 --> 01:02:50.387
It's not the first time I cheated Death.

950
01:02:52.899 --> 01:02:55.852
A kid came to school with a knife...

951
01:02:55.943 --> 01:02:57.735
killed his teacher.

952
01:02:59.572 --> 01:03:01.695
Teacher would have been me.

953
01:03:01.782 --> 01:03:05.447
but I was transferred to another school two days before.

954
01:03:05.536 --> 01:03:07.659
That's fucking weird. man.

955
01:03:07.746 --> 01:03:09.075
You want weird?

956
01:03:09.164 --> 01:03:11.240
Last year my partner and I were heading out

957
01:03:11.333 --> 01:03:13.409
when a call came in about a train wreck.

958
01:03:13.502 --> 01:03:15.744
Frank decided to let me handle it alone.

959
01:03:17.840 --> 01:03:19.962
He died that night in a shootout.

960
01:03:21.176 --> 01:03:24.296
If that call had come in just 10 seconds later.

961
01:03:24.388 --> 01:03:26.095
I'd be dead. too.

962
01:03:26.181 --> 01:03:28.304
Oh my God.

963
01:03:28.391 --> 01:03:30.301
I'm sorry.

964
01:03:30.393 --> 01:03:32.018
It's just I got one. too.

965
01:03:32.103 --> 01:03:34.226
Okay. so last May I'm supposed to go and stay

966
01:03:34.314 --> 01:03:36.983
at this cheesy little bed and breakfast in Pennsylvania.

967
01:03:37.067 --> 01:03:39.984
Anyhow. there's this major gas leak that no one knows about.

968
01:03:40.069 --> 01:03:42.477
and all the guests suffocated during the night.

969
01:03:42.572 --> 01:03:43.852
So what happened?

970
01:03:43.948 --> 01:03:45.526
I don't know.
I never made it.

971
01:03:45.617 --> 01:03:48.321
The bus I was on splattered some girl all over the road.

972
01:03:48.411 --> 01:03:49.822
Was that in Mt Abraham?

973
01:03:49.912 --> 01:03:53.328
Yes. How did you know?

974
01:03:53.416 --> 01:03:56.037
That bus you were on killed Terry Chaney.

975
01:03:57.420 --> 01:03:59.708
She was supposed to die on Flight 180.

976
01:04:02.758 --> 01:04:05.629
Hey. do you guys remember that theatre in Paris

977
01:04:05.719 --> 01:04:08.507
that collapsed last year and killed everybody inside?

978
01:04:10.349 --> 01:04:12.638
Well. I had tickets to go.

979
01:04:12.726 --> 01:04:15.134
But one night I'm in Paris

980
01:04:15.229 --> 01:04:18.479
and I'm just tripping on acid

981
01:04:18.565 --> 01:04:20.807
and sipping lattes and such.

982
01:04:20.901 --> 01:04:22.728
And then all of a sudden

983
01:04:22.819 --> 01:04:25.986
this dude out of nowhere

984
01:04:26.073 --> 01:04:28.480
just gets whacked by this falling sign.

985
01:04:28.575 --> 01:04:31.327
- Carter.
- Wait. wait. wait.

986
01:04:31.411 --> 01:04:33.984
The teacher I replaced. her name was Val Lewton.

987
01:04:34.080 --> 01:04:35.453
She was from Mt Abraham.

988
01:04:35.479 --> 01:04:37.023
She died in an explosion.

989
01:04:37.083 --> 01:04:40.001
Shit. The call about the train wreck

990
01:04:40.086 --> 01:04:41.664
that saved my life...

991
01:04:41.755 --> 01:04:44.162
that was the night I scraped up Billy Hitchcock.

992
01:04:44.257 --> 01:04:45.186
Wait a minute.

993
01:04:45.212 --> 01:04:46.738
Who are these people?

994
01:04:48.219 --> 01:04:50.212
The people who got off of Flight 180.

995
01:04:51.889 --> 01:04:54.048
They were my friends.

996
01:04:57.520 --> 01:04:59.809
Kimberly. tell us what happened.

997
01:05:02.984 --> 01:05:06.103
About a year ago my mum and I were at the mall.

998
01:05:06.195 --> 01:05:08.104
I was supposed to meet her outside.

999
01:05:08.197 --> 01:05:10.770
but I got caught up watching this news report

1000
01:05:10.866 --> 01:05:12.740
about some kid that committed suicide.

1001
01:05:14.161 --> 01:05:15.952
I kept thinking.

1002
01:05:16.038 --> 01:05:18.410
'How can you strangle yourself in the bathtub?

1003
01:05:18.499 --> 01:05:20.325
That's stupid.'

1004
01:05:23.003 --> 01:05:24.960
It felt wrong.

1005
01:05:25.047 --> 01:05:26.838
And yet...

1006
01:05:29.843 --> 01:05:33.129
I heard some gunshots and I ran outside.

1007
01:05:35.182 --> 01:05:37.803
Some kids were trying to steal my mum's car.

1008
01:05:37.893 --> 01:05:40.466
She tried to fight them off. she was a fighter.

1009
01:05:40.562 --> 01:05:42.638
and they killed her.

1010
01:05:44.190 --> 01:05:47.855
After the funeral I kept thinking that it should have been me.

1011
01:05:49.529 --> 01:05:51.356
I guess everyone must think that.

1012
01:05:52.991 --> 01:05:55.030
But I guess I was right.

1013
01:06:04.168 --> 01:06:07.252
Get there.
Could you drive a little faster maybe?!

1014
01:06:07.338 --> 01:06:09.081
- I'm going as fast as I can.
- God!

1015
01:06:11.300 --> 01:06:13.423
When we got off Flight 180.

1016
01:06:13.511 --> 01:06:16.428
it didn't just change our lives.

1017
01:06:16.514 --> 01:06:18.921
It affected everyone and everything

1018
01:06:19.016 --> 01:06:21.258
we've come into contact with since.

1019
01:06:21.352 --> 01:06:23.261
I'm not sure I'm understanding you.

1020
01:06:23.353 --> 01:06:25.761
Being alive after we were supposed to die.

1021
01:06:25.856 --> 01:06:27.932
it caused an outward ripple.

1022
01:06:28.025 --> 01:06:29.898
A rift in Death's design.

1023
01:06:29.985 --> 01:06:32.986
So if you had never gotten off the plane...

1024
01:06:34.489 --> 01:06:36.612
we wouldn't be alive in the first place.

1025
01:06:36.700 --> 01:06:39.238
Yes. that's why Death is working backwards!

1026
01:06:39.327 --> 01:06:41.450
It's tying up all the loose ends.

1027
01:06:41.538 --> 01:06:43.827
Sealing the rift once and for all.

1028
01:07:05.812 --> 01:07:07.222
Oh. shit!

1029
01:07:09.315 --> 01:07:10.939
Jesus Christ!

1030
01:07:13.569 --> 01:07:15.526
Hang on! Hang on!

1031
01:07:35.674 --> 01:07:37.999
- Is everybody alright?
- Oh God.

1032
01:07:40.345 --> 01:07:42.053
God. Eugene!

1033
01:07:42.139 --> 01:07:45.258
- He can't breathe.
- Oh. my legs!

1034
01:07:48.186 --> 01:07:49.811
No. please.

1035
01:07:49.896 --> 01:07:50.982
It's not going to wait.

1036
01:07:51.008 --> 01:07:52.708
I got to go help those people.

1037
01:07:52.774 --> 01:07:54.980
Do you want to deliver this baby?

1038
01:07:56.569 --> 01:07:59.404
Those people can help.
Let's go.

1039
01:08:01.032 --> 01:08:03.404
Officer Adams reporting a vehicle collision

1040
01:08:03.493 --> 01:08:05.569
off 9-A at the 180 mile-marker.

1041
01:08:05.661 --> 01:08:07.488
Send all emergency vehicles to the scene.

1042
01:08:07.580 --> 01:08:08.913
We have to go. Go!

1043
01:08:08.939 --> 01:08:10.641
Okay. okay. okay!

1044
01:08:10.708 --> 01:08:11.810
Just... okay. okay!

1045
01:08:11.836 --> 01:08:13.402
We're going! We're going!

1046
01:08:15.129 --> 01:08:18.046
- Easy. easy.
- Here. here. here.

1047
01:08:18.132 --> 01:08:20.338
I think he has a collapsed lung.

1048
01:08:20.426 --> 01:08:21.361
Everyone okay?

1049
01:08:21.387 --> 01:08:22.989
Call an ambulance!

1050
01:08:28.142 --> 01:08:30.383
Stay with us.

1051
01:08:30.477 --> 01:08:31.853
Hey. hey you!

1052
01:08:31.937 --> 01:08:33.862
Hey! Come on.

1053
01:08:33.888 --> 01:08:35.960
Help me out.

1054
01:08:36.024 --> 01:08:39.607
You got to get me out of here before this thing explodes or something. okay?

1055
01:08:42.406 --> 01:08:43.900
I think it's okay.

1056
01:08:43.990 --> 01:08:46.279
I don't smell any gas and nothing's dripping.

1057
01:08:46.368 --> 01:08:48.074
Alright. get this thing off me.

1058
01:08:48.100 --> 01:08:49.144
Just pull.
Hurry.

1059
01:08:49.204 --> 01:08:51.327
Okay. Be careful.
Ready?

1060
01:08:52.832 --> 01:08:55.786
Oh God. Jethro!
Jesus Christ!

1061
01:08:55.877 --> 01:08:58.119
I got to be able to use my legs when I'm done.

1062
01:08:58.213 --> 01:09:00.289
I'm so... Dad!

1063
01:09:06.512 --> 01:09:08.090
Eugene. everything's going to be okay.

1064
01:09:08.181 --> 01:09:10.932
If he doesn't get a respirator. he's not going to make it!

1065
01:09:11.017 --> 01:09:12.899
We're going to get you to the hospital.

1066
01:09:12.925 --> 01:09:13.959
Be careful with that!

1067
01:09:14.020 --> 01:09:17.471
Check the gauges on the regulator. and watch out for overdoses!

1068
01:09:17.565 --> 01:09:19.334
And look out for potholes and puddles.

1069
01:09:19.360 --> 01:09:20.674
You can't come in. miss.

1070
01:09:22.319 --> 01:09:24.561
And watch out for power lines!

1071
01:09:25.990 --> 01:09:27.982
Watch it!

1072
01:09:33.497 --> 01:09:35.953
You trying to get yourself killed. little boy?

1073
01:09:36.041 --> 01:09:38.330
You got to use your head. man.

1074
01:09:38.418 --> 01:09:40.126
Get that news van back.

1075
01:09:40.212 --> 01:09:41.789
Thanks.

1076
01:09:49.513 --> 01:09:51.173
Okay. let's go.

1077
01:10:07.488 --> 01:10:09.861
How is she doing?

1078
01:10:09.949 --> 01:10:12.025
I think she's going to be okay.

1079
01:10:14.871 --> 01:10:17.540
- Can I ask you a question?
- Yeah.

1080
01:10:19.542 --> 01:10:21.499
When I die...

1081
01:10:21.585 --> 01:10:23.377
is it going to hurt?

1082
01:10:24.880 --> 01:10:26.707
I don't know.

1083
01:10:28.217 --> 01:10:30.044
You're going to die after me. right?

1084
01:10:31.220 --> 01:10:33.047
Yeah. I guess so.

1085
01:10:35.057 --> 01:10:37.050
Would you take these?

1086
01:10:42.898 --> 01:10:44.807
And if I die...

1087
01:10:47.569 --> 01:10:49.360
would you throw out all my drugs

1088
01:10:49.446 --> 01:10:53.396
and my paraphernalia and my porno?

1089
01:10:55.744 --> 01:10:57.368
You know...

1090
01:10:57.454 --> 01:10:59.909
anything that's going to break my mum's heart.

1091
01:11:01.082 --> 01:11:02.826
Please?

1092
01:11:06.171 --> 01:11:07.831
Thank you.

1093
01:11:12.176 --> 01:11:13.968
This is Cheyenne Jacobson

1094
01:11:14.053 --> 01:11:15.962
reporting live from the Gibbons farm.

1095
01:11:16.055 --> 01:11:17.799
Sheriff Perry. Officer Burke here.

1096
01:11:17.890 --> 01:11:20.464
I'm trying to get some information on Isabella...

1097
01:11:20.560 --> 01:11:22.469
She did?

1098
01:11:22.562 --> 01:11:25.135
Okay. Thanks.
Great.

1099
01:11:25.231 --> 01:11:26.690
Kimberly!

1100
01:11:26.774 --> 01:11:28.007
Isabella's at Lakeview Hospital.

1101
01:11:28.033 --> 01:11:29.420
They're prepping her for delivery.

1102
01:11:29.485 --> 01:11:30.339
We got to go now.

1103
01:11:30.365 --> 01:11:31.419
What about Kat?

1104
01:11:31.487 --> 01:11:32.732
I'll go talk to her.

1105
01:11:32.822 --> 01:11:35.657
Hi.

1106
01:11:35.741 --> 01:11:38.279
Just find Isabella and get this thing over with. okay?

1107
01:11:38.369 --> 01:11:40.112
Go on. I'll be fine.

1108
01:11:47.044 --> 01:11:49.036
- Where's Rory?
- I don't know.

1109
01:11:53.175 --> 01:11:55.962
Could you be a little quieter with that thing. please?

1110
01:11:56.052 --> 01:11:58.923
Yeah. sure.
I'll just put it on quiet mode.

1111
01:11:59.014 --> 01:12:00.389
That would be good.

1112
01:12:28.584 --> 01:12:29.663
Rory.

1113
01:12:45.726 --> 01:12:48.015
Oh my God!

1114
01:12:48.103 --> 01:12:50.096
Somebody get out there!

1115
01:12:50.189 --> 01:12:51.932
We have to get to the hospital now!

1116
01:12:51.958 --> 01:12:53.167
Well. take my truck!

1117
01:12:53.233 --> 01:12:54.692
The keys are in it.

1118
01:12:58.530 --> 01:13:00.855
Kimberly!

1119
01:13:12.043 --> 01:13:13.418
Kimberly!

1120
01:13:13.503 --> 01:13:15.626
- Kimberly.
- What do you see?

1121
01:13:15.713 --> 01:13:17.053
What are we looking for?

1122
01:13:17.079 --> 01:13:18.194
It's not here.

1123
01:13:20.009 --> 01:13:21.966
This one was different.

1124
01:13:22.053 --> 01:13:25.007
It was like the van crashing into the lake.

1125
01:13:25.098 --> 01:13:27.137
I was in a hospital. there was screaming

1126
01:13:27.225 --> 01:13:28.933
and a nurse was trying to choke me.

1127
01:13:29.018 --> 01:13:31.591
I couldn't see her. but I could see her name tag.

1128
01:13:31.687 --> 01:13:33.644
It was right in my face.
Kalarjian.

1129
01:13:35.358 --> 01:13:38.561
I think a nurse named Kalarjian is going to try and kill Isabella.

1130
01:13:42.573 --> 01:13:43.863
Listen to me. Isabella!

1131
01:13:43.889 --> 01:13:45.515
I need you to stop pushing!

1132
01:13:45.576 --> 01:13:46.147
What's wrong?

1133
01:13:46.173 --> 01:13:47.095
Is my baby alright?

1134
01:13:47.161 --> 01:13:48.393
The cord's around the neck.

1135
01:13:48.419 --> 01:13:49.558
This baby's in trouble.

1136
01:13:49.621 --> 01:13:52.492
A bizarre accident has left two people dead.

1137
01:13:52.583 --> 01:13:55.418
one of them killed by a safety device meant to protect us.

1138
01:13:55.502 --> 01:13:57.958
Ironically. the woman was impaled through the head

1139
01:13:58.046 --> 01:14:00.371
after her emergency airbag deployed.

1140
01:14:00.465 --> 01:14:04.048
She was trapped in her vehicle after it
crashed into a field near Greenwood Lake.

1141
01:14:04.136 --> 01:14:06.543
Suddenly the airbag went off...

1142
01:14:41.005 --> 01:14:43.081
Isabella Hudson!
What room is she in?

1143
01:14:43.174 --> 01:14:45.250
We may need to do a stat Caesarean!

1144
01:14:45.342 --> 01:14:47.169
Get Dr. Kalarjian up here now!

1145
01:14:47.261 --> 01:14:49.930
Dr. Kalarjian. code blue.
Delivery room six.

1146
01:14:50.014 --> 01:14:51.424
I'm just going to wait outside.

1147
01:14:51.515 --> 01:14:53.472
'cause I'm just really in the way here.

1148
01:14:53.559 --> 01:14:55.468
- Don't you dare leave me!
- Okay. okay.

1149
01:14:55.561 --> 01:14:57.304
You guys. get to Isabella!

1150
01:14:57.396 --> 01:14:59.187
I'm going to find Eugene!

1151
01:14:59.273 --> 01:15:01.032
Dr. Kalarjian. code blue.

1152
01:15:01.058 --> 01:15:02.464
Delivery room six.

1153
01:15:02.526 --> 01:15:05.480
Dr. Kalarjian. delivery room six.
Code blue.

1154
01:15:21.169 --> 01:15:23.494
Dr. Kalarjian. in here. hurry!

1155
01:15:24.672 --> 01:15:26.795
That's her.

1156
01:15:27.842 --> 01:15:29.420
Wait. wait. wait!

1157
01:16:06.672 --> 01:16:08.997
Contractions have stopped.

1158
01:16:09.091 --> 01:16:11.582
Arrest in descent halfway through the birth canal.

1159
01:16:11.676 --> 01:16:13.752
Bad tracing. it's losing oxygen.

1160
01:16:13.845 --> 01:16:15.921
The cord's compressed!

1161
01:16:16.014 --> 01:16:16.854
Down to 40.

1162
01:16:16.880 --> 01:16:19.324
Oh God! What's happening?!

1163
01:16:19.392 --> 01:16:21.100
Where's Kalarjian?!

1164
01:16:21.186 --> 01:16:23.855
Dr. Kalarjian!

1165
01:16:23.938 --> 01:16:26.097
- Dr. Kalarjian!
- Not now. I'm busy.

1166
01:16:26.191 --> 01:16:29.394
- Ow! Hey! Hey!
- Police business.

1167
01:16:38.661 --> 01:16:41.234
Just push a little more.

1168
01:16:41.330 --> 01:16:43.655
Oh. no.

1169
01:16:43.749 --> 01:16:45.493
Isabella. is the baby okay?

1170
01:16:46.669 --> 01:16:47.210
I'm sorry.

1171
01:16:47.236 --> 01:16:48.318
You can't be here.

1172
01:16:48.379 --> 01:16:49.768
I have to ask you to leave.

1173
01:16:49.794 --> 01:16:50.977
I need to know...

1174
01:16:51.048 --> 01:16:53.919
I need to know if the baby's alright!

1175
01:16:55.511 --> 01:16:57.338
It's a boy.

1176
01:17:18.116 --> 01:17:20.073
Thank you.
Congratulations!

1177
01:17:20.160 --> 01:17:22.117
Who the hell are they?

1178
01:17:22.203 --> 01:17:24.576
Oh my God!

1179
01:17:28.293 --> 01:17:30.119
- Clear.
- I can't find Eugene.

1180
01:17:30.211 --> 01:17:32.916
- No. don't worry. She had the baby!
- It's okay.

1181
01:17:33.006 --> 01:17:34.963
It's over.
It's okay.

1182
01:17:48.479 --> 01:17:50.887
- Kimberly.
- What did you see?

1183
01:17:50.981 --> 01:17:54.267
I don't think Isabella was ever supposed to die in that pileup.

1184
01:17:54.360 --> 01:17:56.685
Then what's the premonition of the lake supposed to mean?

1185
01:17:56.779 --> 01:17:58.606
Try to remember.

1186
01:18:15.964 --> 01:18:19.250
Bloody hands.
Someone with bloody hands.

1187
01:18:20.302 --> 01:18:21.712
Eugene.

1188
01:18:26.182 --> 01:18:27.622
Only new life defeats death.

1189
01:18:27.648 --> 01:18:29.292
What is that supposed to mean?

1190
01:18:29.352 --> 01:18:31.144
You saw an ECG machine and what else?

1191
01:18:33.148 --> 01:18:35.306
Bloody hands.
What else did you see. Kimberly?

1192
01:18:36.359 --> 01:18:37.818
Wait.

1193
01:18:39.779 --> 01:18:41.606
Eugene.

1194
01:19:01.759 --> 01:19:03.668
Oh God. no!

1195
01:19:13.937 --> 01:19:15.645
Bloody hands.

1196
01:19:17.441 --> 01:19:19.564
It's me.
The premonitions are about me.

1197
01:19:19.651 --> 01:19:21.727
- What?
- Crash cart.

1198
01:19:21.820 --> 01:19:23.279
Let's go! Move it!

1199
01:19:25.574 --> 01:19:27.531
Dr. Kalarjian.

1200
01:19:27.617 --> 01:19:29.409
ECG machine.

1201
01:19:33.915 --> 01:19:35.575
The lake.

1202
01:19:35.667 --> 01:19:37.540
The white van.

1203
01:19:42.298 --> 01:19:44.125
What are you talking about?

1204
01:19:46.803 --> 01:19:48.629
New life.

1205
01:19:51.182 --> 01:19:52.925
What is it?

1206
01:19:53.017 --> 01:19:55.306
I know what I have to do to save us.

1207
01:19:56.812 --> 01:19:57.930
I have to die.

1208
01:19:57.956 --> 01:19:59.791
No. that's crazy.

1209
01:19:59.857 --> 01:20:01.177
You can't give up now.

1210
01:20:01.203 --> 01:20:03.002
We have to fight this thing.

1211
01:20:07.656 --> 01:20:09.649
Get Kalarjian.

1212
01:22:35.175 --> 01:22:38.259
Only new life can defeat death.

1213
01:22:38.345 --> 01:22:41.096
If it is my time to go and be in heaven...

1214
01:22:41.181 --> 01:22:43.506
..with my family.
I can accept that.

1215
01:22:45.143 --> 01:22:46.803
Flight 180...

1216
01:22:46.895 --> 01:22:49.136
I know what I have to do to save us.

1217
01:22:49.230 --> 01:22:51.306
There are no known survivors.

1218
01:22:51.399 --> 01:22:53.356
I have to die.

1219
01:22:54.902 --> 01:22:57.572
Ready and clear!

1220
01:22:58.614 --> 01:22:59.694
Nothing!

1221
01:23:02.618 --> 01:23:04.777
Ready and clear.

1222
01:23:06.289 --> 01:23:08.115
Nothing.

1223
01:23:09.500 --> 01:23:11.908
- Come on.
- Ready. clear.

1224
01:23:12.002 --> 01:23:15.039
She's back!

1225
01:23:15.130 --> 01:23:17.419
Epinephrine.
Two milligrams. IV push.

1226
01:23:17.508 --> 01:23:20.343
I want her prepped and stabilized for ICU.

1227
01:23:24.473 --> 01:23:26.133
Welcome back.

1228
01:23:27.309 --> 01:23:29.385
They lost you for a minute there.

1229
01:23:35.484 --> 01:23:38.734
Hey. We did it.

1230
01:23:39.821 --> 01:23:41.814
Thanks to you. we cheated Death.

1231
01:24:14.313 --> 01:24:16.021
Would you like some wine?

1232
01:24:16.107 --> 01:24:18.229
I think I'll stick to our beer. thanks.

1233
01:24:18.317 --> 01:24:19.645
Alright.

1234
01:24:19.735 --> 01:24:22.143
This is really great. Mrs. Gibbons.

1235
01:24:22.238 --> 01:24:24.396
Thank you so much for inviting us.

1236
01:24:24.490 --> 01:24:26.399
It's our pleasure.

1237
01:24:27.659 --> 01:24:31.075
- How are you doing. Kimberly?
- Good. Yeah.

1238
01:24:31.163 --> 01:24:33.321
I had a fun summer.

1239
01:24:33.415 --> 01:24:36.701
I don't know. I guess things are pretty much getting back to normal.

1240
01:24:39.463 --> 01:24:42.499
Brian. I think you better go check that barbecue.

1241
01:24:42.591 --> 01:24:45.212
Hey. careful.
Those things are dangerous.

1242
01:24:45.302 --> 01:24:47.508
Trust me.
I think I've been through closer calls.

1243
01:24:47.596 --> 01:24:48.203
Yeah. me too.

1244
01:24:48.229 --> 01:24:50.657
Dad. you should tell them about the news van thing.

1245
01:24:50.724 --> 01:24:52.467
What's that?

1246
01:24:52.559 --> 01:24:55.809
Brian was almost hit by that news van that day in the field.

1247
01:24:55.895 --> 01:24:58.565
And your friend Rory. he pulled him back at the last second.

1248
01:24:58.648 --> 01:24:59.677
Saved his life.

1249
01:24:59.703 --> 01:25:02.172
You never told me that. Peter.

1250
01:25:02.235 --> 01:25:03.777
Boy. that was lucky.

1251
01:25:08.616 --> 01:25:10.941
Brian!

